    "Such an approach not only enhances the accuracy and realism of our simulations but also underscores the practical applicability of FCL in addressing computational challenges.",
    "Collision Detection Case Study (CD): Collision Detection with Two Cylinders and One BoxThe CD case study explores the application of the FCL to model a scenario involving two mobile cylinders and one stationary box, each with dimensions of one meter across their respective axes.",
    "This scenario, depicted in Figure 4.1, serves as a simplified yet insightful exploration into dynamic collision detection's computational demands and accuracy within constrained environments.",
    "Based on discussions with our industry partner, we chose to develop this case study, which models two robots as cylinders and an object in the environment as a stable, unmoving box.",
    "In robotic systems, complex objects are often simplified into basic shapes to expedite collision detection and reduce computational demands."
